:) Yeah it wont work, object key is `Op.or` so last one will always override. For example

```js
{
  a: 1,
  a: 2
}
```
 will always give you

```js
{
  a: 2
}
```

For your usecase, perhaps wrap both `Op.or` blocks under `Op.and`

```js
{
  where: {
    checkedAt: null,
    abcId: {
      [Op.not]: null
    },
    [Op.and]: [{
        [Op.or]: [{
          cancelledAt: {
            [Op.lt]: moment().subtract(3, 'minutes')
          }
        }, {
          [Op.and]: [{
            orderId: null
          }, {
            orderDate: {
              [Op.lt]: moment().subtract(2, 'hours')
            }
