If you do no specify a charset when creating your table or in the define options or your sequelize options, the table will be created with the default charset for the DB.

There are several things you can do to support unicode:

Table level:

``` js
sequlize.define('table', {

}, {
  charset: 'utf8',
  collate: 'utf8_unicode_ci'
})
```

Column level:

``` js
sequelize.define('table', {
  column: Sequelize.STRING + ' CHARSET utf8 COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci'
})
